gomodel:SYNGO_3122  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Abstract: \"We have used a retroviral cDNA expression system to drive the expression of the different forms of glutamic acid decarboxylase (GAD65, GAD67, or both). Individual clones of engineered Rat-1 cells make the appropriate GAD mRNAs and GAD polypeptides, show GAD enzymatic activity, and make GABA.\"\n\nNote:\n- GAD's glutamate decarboxylase activity converts L-Glutamate into 4-aminobutanoate (GABA).\n- The neurotransmitter role of GABA in the CNS is well established.\n- This activity is not shown in vivo in any known publications known at the time of this writing.. Experimental description: - Overexpressed GAD1; GAD67 is of human species." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3122" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

